The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Last quarter saves the day for Indian Oil
                                                                                                               Last quarter saves the day for Indian Oil
                              Sarthak Behuria in New Delhi on Friday. Picture by Rajesh Kumar                            
	New Delhi, May 29 (PTI): Indian Oil Corporation today reported a net profit of Rs 6,622.96 crore in the fourth quarter of 2008-09, helping the company to end the fiscal in black.        
	IOC had reported a net loss of Rs 7,047 crore in the second quarter and a net profit of Rs 415 crore and Rs 2959 crore in the first quarter and the third quarter, respectively.        
	For the fiscal, IOC posted a net profit of Rs 2,599.40 crore, which was lower than Rs 7,912.74 crore in 2007-08, IOC chairman Sarthak Behuria told reporters here.        
	The profits were possible because of the Rs 40,383-crore special oil bonds issued by (the) government and Rs 18,210 crore assistance received from upstream companies, he said.        
	During the last fiscal, the company had lost Rs 58,593 crore in revenues on the sale of auto and cooking fuel. After taking into account the bonds and assistance from upstream firms, the net revenue loss was Rs 9,774 crore.        
	During the fourth quarter, IOC earned $4.5 by processing every barrel of crude against a gross refining margin (GRM) of $8.67 per barrel in the same period last fiscal. For the full year, the company earned GRM of $3.69 per barrel against $9.02 in the previous year.         
	BPCL net jumps         
	Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd (BPCL) today reported a 62-fold growth in net profit at Rs 3,628.02 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2009.        
	The oil major had a net profit of Rs 58.39 crore in the March quarter of 2007-08, the company said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange.        
	Total income declined 17.11 per cent to Rs 27,115.38 crore in the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2009, from Rs 32,712.92 crore in the corresponding period a year-ago.                                                                                                                                             
